<article>
    <h1>IF YOU WANT TO TAKE UP DESERT TRAIL RUN&#xAD;NING</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20210102/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2021-01-02"><time>2021-01-02</time></a>
        - <span>SPORT</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>HOW</p>
    <p>Start with trail runs and ul­tra­ma­rathons first and race in dif­fer­ent places with dif­fer­ent ter­rains. Do your re­search and con­sult oth­ers who have par­tic­i­pated in desert races for tips and ad­vice.</p>
    <p>Test your gear and equip­ment be­fore you pack them into your back­pack. Try dif­fer­ent race food and drinks to find out what works for you.</p>
    <p>WHERE</p>
    <p>Some of the key desert races are: the Marathon des Sables in the Sa­hara, Bad­wa­ter 135 in Cal­i­for­nia and the 4 Deserts Ul­tra­ma­rathon Se­ries in Namibia, Gobi, Ata­cama and Antarc­tica.</p>
    <p>WHERE TO BUY EQUIP­MENT</p>
    <p>Campers’ Cor­ner, Out­door Life, Red Dot Run­ning Com­pany, Run­ning Lab.</p>
    <p>COST</p>
    <p>€3,170 (S$5,083) regis­tra­tion fee for the Marathon des Sables. Regis­tra­tion fees for the 4 Deserts Se­ries: Namibia (US$3,800), Gobi (US$3,800), Ata­cama (US$3,800), Antarc­tica (US$12,900).</p>
    <p>*Air­fare is not in­cluded</p>


